
---
// src/pages/projects/copybot.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="CopyBot - Solana Wallet & PNL Tracker" backgroundColor="#412E20">
  <main class="project-detail-container">
    <article class="project-detail" transition:name="copybot">
      <a href="/projects" class="back-link">
        <span class="arrow">←</span>
        <span>back to projects</span>
      </a>

      <div class="project-header">
        <h1>CopyBot</h1>
        <span class="tag">Python · Blockchain · Data</span>
      </div>

      <p class="project-intro">
        A Python-based system for monitoring, analyzing, and optimizing Solana copy-trading wallets
        using real-time on-chain data and post-trade performance tracking.
      </p>

      <div class="project-content">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          CopyBot is a multi-service Solana analytics tool designed to evaluate the effectiveness of
          copy-trading strategies. It ingests real-time wallet activity via webhooks, enriches trades
          with market and risk data, and tracks post-purchase token performance using delayed OHLCV
          analysis.
        </p>
        <p>
          Based on historical performance, the system periodically identifies underperforming or
          inactive wallets and replaces them with higher-performing candidates sourced from on-chain
          analytics platforms. The project emphasizes automation, asynchronous execution, and
          data-driven decision-making. The current version is under active rewrite, with core logic
          being refactored for robustness and scalability.
        </p>

        <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
        <div class="project-tech">
          <span>Python 3</span>
          <span>Asyncio</span>
          <span>Discord.py</span>
          <span>Pandas</span>
          <span>Selenium</span>
          <span>Helius API</span>
          <span>Bitquery</span>
          <span>Dune Analytics</span>
          <span>Alchemy</span>
          <span>Jupiter API</span>
          <span>DexScreener</span>
        </div>

        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Real-time Solana wallet monitoring via Helius webhooks</li>
          <li>Trade parsing and enrichment with pricing, metadata, and risk scores</li>
          <li>Delayed OHLCV-based PNL tracking for first-holder entries</li>
          <li>Automated wallet performance evaluation and replacement logic</li>
          <li>Discord-based alerts and reporting pipeline</li>
          <li>Modular, scheduled async bot architecture</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Challenges & Solutions</h2>
        <p>
          The main challenge was coordinating multiple data sources with different latency and rate
          limits while maintaining consistent state across services. This was addressed by
          decoupling ingestion, analysis, and optimization into independent bots orchestrated through
          an asynchronous scheduler and lightweight local data stores.
        </p>

        <div class="project-links">
          <a 
             href="https://github.com/snezzz0/solana-wallet-tracker-old/" class="project-link-btn"
             target="_blank"
             rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span>View Code</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .project-detail-container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .back-link {
    position: absolute;
    top: -3rem;
    left: 0;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    color: #FFE4AF;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    transition: color 0.2s;
    z-index: 10;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: #EC753A;
  }

  .arrow {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-detail {
    background: #412E20;
    border: 3px solid #DA9F5F;
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    width: 100%;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .project-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .project-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #FFE4AF;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tag {
    background: #DA9F5F;
    color: #342331;
    padding: 0.4rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid #EC753A;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .project-intro {
    color: #DA9F5F;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .project-content h2 {
    color: #FFE4AF;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project-content p {
    color: #DA9F5F;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-tech {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .project-tech span {
    background: rgba(218, 159, 95, 0.2);
    color: #DA9F5F;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid #DA9F5F;
  }

  .project-content ul {
    color: #DA9F5F;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .project-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .project-link-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    color: #EC753A;
    border: 2px solid #EC753A;
    padding: 1rem 1.75rem;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .project-link-btn:hover {
    background: #EC753A;
    color: #342331;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project-detail-container {
      padding: 3rem 1rem 2rem;
    }

    .back-link {
      top: -2.5rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .project-detail {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .project-header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .project-header h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .project-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .project-link-btn {
      width: 100%;
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>

